THE ATOMIC TRINITY (PROTON, ELECTRON, NEUTRON)

The Three Components of an Atom

• An atom is generally made up of three components:
  1. The POSITIVELY charged PROTON
  2. The NEGATIVELY charged ELECTRON
  3. The NEUTRAL NEUTRON

• Aptly named - these names directly reflect their energetic nature

How Apt and Expressive This Structure Is

• This structure is expressive in a very specific and precise way to the energy patterns described
• The atomic structure is not random - it precisely mirrors the energetic structure of consciousness itself
• This is a direct physical manifestation of metaphysical principles

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

THE NEUTRAL NEUTRON BREAKS DOWN

The Critical Discovery About Neutrons

• A neutron, if left to its own devices (a free neutron not connected within an atomic structure), actually BREAKS DOWN into a proton and an electron
• This is a crucial point that reveals the nature of the neutral state

Why the Neutron is Neutral

• The neutral particle is neutral because it is made up of:
  - Positive charges
  - Negative charges
• It expresses these things and manifests these things as the two seemingly opposite elementary particles:
  - The proton (positive)
  - The electron (negative)

The Neutron Contains Both Charges

• Because it contains both charges, it is able to:
  - Be attracted to the proton
  - Attract a proton to it
  - As well as attract the electron
• The neutron has "layers" to it energetically (this is somewhat euphemistic but a good way to illustrate the point)

═══════════════════════════════════════════════════════════

THE NEUTRON'S LAYER STRUCTURE

How the Neutron Attracts Both Particles

• The neutron being neutral because it contains both charges does this in a particular way
• Sort of like a "layer cake"

Why Layers Are Necessary

• The proton cannot be attracted to another positively charged particle easily
• The neutron must attract it
• If it is to attract the proton at all, it must have some kind of charge with which to do so

The Skin and Body of the Neutron

• The SKIN of the neutron (so to speak) is actually NEGATIVELY charged to attract the proton
• But it is also in its BODY POSITIVELY charged to also attract the electron
• So it does double duty in this way
• This creates and gives structure to the concept that you call the atom

The Mass of the Neutron

• Because the neutron is able to break down into the proton and the electron (and a few other things not discussed here)
• You begin to understand that the neutron is, in a sense, a little bit bigger than both of them
• It has more mass than the proton
• Way more mass than the electron
• But it contains both
• So it has to be more massive than both so that when it breaks down, there is sufficient amount of mass to express the proton and the electron

