THE ELECTRON REPRESENTS NEGATIVE BELIEFS

The Electron as Negative Energy

• The electron is representative of the idea of negative energy
• When talking about it as an energetic state, Bashar is talking about:
  - That which is disconnective
  - Dissociative
  - Segregative (so to speak)

The Proton as Positive Energy

• By contrast, positive energy is about things that are:
  - Integrative
  - Expansive
  - Connective (as a mechanism)

Negative Energy and Negative Beliefs

• Associated with negative energy are negative beliefs
• Belief systems, both positive and negative, must do something to perpetuate themselves
• Because they're not really real
• Physical reality is not really real in a sense - it's a projection, a dream, an illusion

How Belief Systems Perpetuate Themselves

• Belief systems are designed to perpetuate themselves in such a manner as to make it seem as if:
  - The reality that they depict is actually real
  - The definition of reality that they depict is actually real
• So that you can have an actual solid physical experience

Positive Beliefs vs. Negative Beliefs

**Positive Beliefs:**
• Positive beliefs reflect to you the true nature of your being
• The true powerful, self-empowered, creative, loving nature of your spirit
• The true nature of your being, essence, existence

**Negative Beliefs:**
• Negative belief systems have to work MUCH HARDER than positive beliefs
• They must get you to buy into a scenario that is fundamentally NOT TRUE about you
• Because you are basically creative positive beings essentially

How Negative Beliefs Must Operate

• In order to get you to have an experience that is negative:
  - It has to tell you things that are fundamentally LIES about yourself
  - It has to reinforce those lies with every trick in the book that it can muster
  - Every tool in its kit
• Otherwise, you would see right through the smoke and mirrors
• You would know that it is just an illusion
• You would know that what the negative beliefs are telling you about yourself has to be, by definition, FALSE

